Short answers first:

- **Images:** you‚Äôre **not** guaranteeing ‚Äúno repetition.‚Äù You call `sampleImages()` inside `onStageStart` for **each player**, then always pick `imgs[2]` (because `2 % imgs.length` is always 2). That can repeat across players and stages.  
- **Per-round greeting:** it‚Äôs failing because you read `p.round.get(roundIndex)`, but you set `round.set(roundIndex, i)` on the **round scope**, not the player-round scope. Use `stage.currentRound.get(roundIndex)`.  
- **Greeting list per player:** currently you shuffle **once per game** (`game.set(shuffled_greetings, shuf)`). So no, it‚Äôs not per-player.

---

## Minimal fixes

### 1) Stable, no-repeat avatars (per game)  
If you want unique avatars per player for the whole game, build one deck once and deal them out:

```js
// Build a full deck once
function buildAvatarDeck() {
  const mk = (prefix) => Array.from({ length: 49 }, (_, i) => `${prefix}_${i + 1}.jpg`);
  return shuffled([...mk(man), ...mk(woman), ...mk(neutral)]); // 147 unique
}

Empirica.onGameStart(({ game }) => {
  // ... your round creation ...

  // Per-player greeting order (see ¬ß3)
  for (const p of game.players) {
    p.set(greetings_order, shuffled(greetings));
  }

  // One shared avatar deck for uniqueness across players
  game.set(avatar_deck, buildAvatarDeck());
});
```

Then, in `onStageStart` **don‚Äôt** call `sampleImages()` at all‚Äîpull one from the deck (or assign once per player and reuse):

```js
Empirica.onStageStart(({ stage }) => {
  const game = stage.currentGame;
  const round = stage.currentRound;

  // Correct round index read
  const roundIndex = Number(round.get(roundIndex) ?? 0);

  for (const p of game.players) {
    // Assign a persistent avatar once per player
    if (!p.get(avatar)) {
      const deck = game.get(avatar_deck) || [];
      const img = deck.shift();                 // remove from deck
      game.set(avatar_deck, deck);            // save deck back
      p.set(avatar, img);
      p.set(avatar_url, toPublicPath(img));
    }

    const avatarPath = p.get(avatar_url);

    // Ensure chat array exists
    const attr = chatV2;
    if (!Array.isArray(p.round.get(attr))) p.round.set(attr, []);

    // Kickoff message, per-round greeting pulled from that player's order
    const msgs = p.round.get(attr) || [];
    const already = msgs.some(m => m && m.tag === kickoff && m.for === p.id);

    const order = p.get(greetings_order) || greetings; // per-player shuffle
    const text = order[roundIndex % order.length] || Hi!;

    if (!already) {
      p.round.append(attr, {
        text,
        sender: { id: p.id, name: Other Player, avatar: avatarPath },
        createdAt: Date.now(),
        tag: kickoff,
        for: p.id,
      });
    }
  }
});
```

### 2) If you prefer a simpler ‚Äúone avatar per player, random but not unique‚Äù  
Do it once (not per stage) so it doesn‚Äôt ‚Äúreshuffle‚Äù every time:

```js
Empirica.onGameStart(({ game }) => {
  // ... rounds ...
  for (const p of game.players) {
    const imgList = sampleImages();     // 9 distinct per call
    const chosen = imgList[0];          // pick one deterministically
    p.set(avatar, chosen);
    p.set(avatar_url, toPublicPath(chosen));
    p.set(greetings_order, shuffled(greetings)); // per-player shuffle
  }
});
```

Then in `onStageStart` just read `p.get(avatar_url)` and **don‚Äôt** call `sampleImages()` again.

### 3) Fix the round index source
Replace:
```js
const roundIndex = Number(p.round.get(roundIndex) ?? 0);
```
with:
```js
const roundIndex = Number(stage.currentRound.get(roundIndex) ?? 0);
```
(Or, if you really want it on the player scope, mirror it there when creating rounds.)

---

## Why your current code behaves oddly

- `const imgs = sampleImages(); const image = imgs[2 % imgs.length];`  
  `imgs.length` is 9, so you always pick index **2**. Every player/stage gets the 3rd element of a fresh random 9-pack ‚Üí duplicates are likely.

- `game.set(shuffled_greetings, shuf)` then reading `p.round.get(roundIndex)`  
  `roundIndex` was set on `round`, so `p.round.get(roundIndex)` is undefined. That‚Äôs why your per-round pull ‚Äúisn‚Äôt working.‚Äù Reading from `stage.currentRound.get(...)` fixes it.

- Per-player shuffle: storing on `game` makes a single order shared by all players. Move to `p.set(greetings_order, shuffled(greetings))` to shuffle per player.

If you want, I can tweak this to: (a) prevent avatar reuse across **rounds** too, (b) enforce per-**treatment** uniqueness, or (c) rotate through greetings without modulo wrap.

got it ‚Äî you want **no repeats within a single player across rounds**, but it‚Äôs fine if two different players see the same thing. easiest way: give each player their own pre-shuffled ‚Äúdeck‚Äù for images and greetings, sized to the number of rounds, and index by `roundIndex`.

here‚Äôs a tight patch that does exactly that and also fixes the roundIndex bug:

